output.crosstab_text:
Among those who graduated five years previously from courses in all subjects and who were working during the 2021-22 tax year, the most common industry was Human health and social work activities for First degree graduates, and the most common industry was Education for Level 7 (taught), Level 7 (research) and Level 8 graduates.

The group with the highest earnings was Level 8 graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of £85,400).
